---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SizeGuide from '../components/SizeGuide.astro';
import '../styles/hss-phase1.css';
---

<Layout title="Wedding Invitation Printing Guide | Paper, Sizes & Print Options" description="A simple wedding printing guide for digital invitation templates, including cardstock weights, finishes, envelope sizes, file types, and where to print.">
  <main class="hss-page">
    <section class="hss-hero">
      <div class="hss-container">
        <p class="hss-eyebrow">Printing Guide</p>
        <h1>The simple guide to printing digital wedding invitations.</h1>
        <p class="hss-lead">Not sure what paper to choose or where to print your template? This guide covers the practical basics so your finished stationery feels polished, intentional, and wedding-ready.</p>
        <div class="hss-button-row"><a class="hss-button" href="/shop/">Shop Templates</a><a class="hss-button-secondary" href="/how-it-works/">How Templates Work</a></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="hss-section">
      <div class="hss-container hss-grid">
        <article class="hss-card"><h2>Best cardstock weight</h2><p>For invitations, start around 100 lb to 130 lb cover cardstock. Lighter paper can feel too thin. Very thick paper may need a professional printer.</p></article>
        <article class="hss-card"><h2>Best finish</h2><p>Matte, linen, cotton, or lightly textured paper usually feels more elevated than glossy paper for wedding stationery.</p></article>
        <article class="hss-card"><h2>Best file type</h2><p>PDF is usually best for professional printing. JPG or PNG can work for online printers that request image uploads.</p></article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="hss-section">
      <div class="hss-container">
        <p class="hss-eyebrow">Paper Cheat Sheet</p>
        <h2>Recommended paper options</h2>
        <div class="hss-table-wrap">
          <table class="hss-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Paper Type</th><th>Best For</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>100 lb cover cardstock</td><td>Invitations, details cards, RSVP cards</td><td>A reliable starting point that feels sturdy without becoming difficult to print.</td></tr>
              <tr><td>110 lb cover cardstock</td><td>Wedding invitation suites</td><td>A popular middle-ground option for a polished, quality feel.</td></tr>
              <tr><td>120–130 lb cover cardstock</td><td>Premium invitations and signage</td><td>Feels substantial, but may require professional printing or special printer settings.</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Linen or cotton texture</td><td>Romantic, classic, garden, and fine-art styles</td><td>Adds softness and dimension without needing extra design elements.</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Smooth matte cardstock</td><td>Modern, minimalist, and mid-century designs</td><td>Keeps typography clean and easy to read.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="hss-section">
      <div class="hss-container hss-grid-2">
        <div class="hss-callout"><h2>Where to print</h2><ul class="hss-list"><li>Local print shops for hands-on help and paper samples</li><li>Online wedding printers for convenience and matching envelopes</li><li>Office print centers for simple, budget-friendly runs</li><li>At home for test prints, signs, and small quantities</li></ul></div>
        <div class="hss-callout"><h2>Before you order</h2><ul class="hss-list"><li>Print one proof before ordering the full quantity</li><li>Check spelling, addresses, dates, and times</li><li>Confirm bleed, trim marks, and file type with the printer</li><li>Order extras for keepsakes, mistakes, and last-minute guests</li></ul></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="hss-section">
      <div class="hss-container">
        <p class="hss-eyebrow">Size Guide</p>
        <h2>Common wedding stationery sizes</h2>
        <p>Most wedding invitations are 5&quot; × 7&quot;. RSVP cards are commonly 3.5&quot; × 5&quot;. Always check the exact template listing before buying envelopes.</p>
        <SizeGuide />
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
